Package core

Interface HlaLauncherManagerListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HlaLauncherManagerListener.Adapter
    public interface HlaLauncherManagerListener
    Listener for changes of HlaLauncher instances.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface Description
      static class  HlaLauncherManagerListener.Adapter
      An abstract adapter class that implements the HlaLauncherManagerListener interface with empty methods.

    • Method Detail

      • hlaLauncherDiscovered

        void hlaLauncherDiscovered​(HlaLauncher launcher,
                           HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a new HlaLauncher instance is discovered. A discovered instance is initially within interest.
        Parameters:
        launcher - the object which is discovered
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaLauncherInitialized

        void hlaLauncherInitialized​(HlaLauncher launcher,
                            HlaTimeStamp timeStamp,
                            HlaLogicalTime logicalTime)
        This method is called when a HlaLauncher instance is initialized. An instance is initialized when it has been discovered and all attribute marked with initialized has a value.
        Parameters:
        launcher - the object which is initialized
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated
        logicalTime - the logical time when the update was initiated

      • hlaLauncherInInterest

        void hlaLauncherInInterest​(HlaLauncher launcher,
                           HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a HlaLauncher instance comes within interest. A discovered instance is initially within interest, so this will not be called at the time of discovery.
        Parameters:
        launcher - the object which has come into interest
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaLauncherOutOfInterest

        void hlaLauncherOutOfInterest​(HlaLauncher launcher,
                              HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a HlaLauncher instance goes out of interest.
        Parameters:
        launcher - the object which has gone out of interest
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaLauncherDeleted

        void hlaLauncherDeleted​(HlaLauncher launcher,
                        HlaTimeStamp timeStamp,
                        HlaLogicalTime logicalTime)
        This method is called when a HlaLauncher instance is deleted.
        Parameters:
        launcher - the object which is deleted
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated
        logicalTime - the logical time when the update was initiated
